problems.promptEn:
Let $B_t$ be standard Brownian motion. Decide which processes are Brownian motions:
(a) $-B_t$;
(b) $cB_{t/c^2}$ for a nonzero constant $c$;
(c) $\sqrt t\,B_1$;
(d) $B_{2t}-B_t$.
Justify each answer.

Use Itô's formula to write SDEs for:
(a) $Y_t=B_t^3$;
(b) $Y_t=\exp(\sigma B_t-\frac12\sigma^2t)$;
(c) $Y_t=tB_t$.
